  "upgrade_suggestion": "For modern fidelity, upgrade to the 2016 Pink Floyd Records remaster (PFRLP9, BG24222 cut) — the European Optimal Media pressing (r25885156) is already in this collection. For a better vintage copy, seek an original 1975 US Columbia first pressing (JC 33453, HRM/Hauppauge plant) with first-generation stampers and an earlier lacquer cut.",
  "commentary": "Released in September 1975, *Wish You Were Here* explores themes of alienation and the dehumanizing nature of the music industry. The album’s conceptual focus on \"absence\" is mirrored in its packaging, which originally featured a black shrink-wrap hiding the cover art, and in its lyrical content, particularly the title track and the multi-part \"Shine On You Crazy Diamond.\"\n\n**About this pressing:**\nThis is a 1980s US Columbia reissue, identifiable by the barcode printed on the back cover and the JC/PC prefix on the spine and labels. *Deadwax TBD — check runouts for mastering engineers or pressing plant symbols. Update this section once details are logged.*\n\n### Gemini Notes\n\nReleased in 1975, *Wish You Were Here* is Pink Floyd's tribute to Syd Barrett and a critique of the music industry. This specific pressing is an 80s reissue, identifiable by the barcode on the back cover and the JC/PC prefix on the spine and labels.\n\n**About this pressing:**",
